Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.01,0:00:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are we?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.30,0:00:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I've no doubt that we are those\Nwho will inherit the coming age.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.93,0:00:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Having broken free of the prejudices\Nand discrimination of old,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.18,0:00:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,we will freely, nimbly, and elegantly
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.55,0:00:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,plunge into the unknown.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.22,0:00:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And today, a new comrade\Nhas joined our quest.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.34,0:00:27.49,Default,,0,0,0,,His name is Albert.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.49,0:00:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.04,0:00:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We're glad to have you!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.91,0:00:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I've served as his tutor,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.78,0:00:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and his clear thinking has amazed me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.78,0:00:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It's as if a master theoretician
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.33,0:00:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,has entered into a young boy's body.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.05,0:00:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,However, what I find even more remarkable
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.05,0:00:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,is his intense curiosity.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.70,0:00:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,No other talent
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.55,0:00:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,is more important\Nto the future of academia.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.23,0:00:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I say that because I am afraid.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.60,0:01:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps in the future,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.47,0:01:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the view that truth is conceived,\Nrather than discovered,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.44,0:01:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}may become an assumption of sorts.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.12,0:01:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Written works of the past\Nand other countries
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.53,0:01:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,all describe different histories,\Ncultures, and faiths.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.12,0:01:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Information is in short supply now,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.56,0:01:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,but if we connect with those\Nforeign to us in the days to come,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.62,0:01:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,even truth may one day\Nbe seen as relative.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.26,0:01:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,When that happens,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.30,0:01:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,awe and admiration\Nfor the ideal of universal truth
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.43,0:01:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,may fade from human hearts.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.98,0:01:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,As a result, research will become\Nincreasingly specialized.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.59,0:01:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The grand desire for contact\Nwith knowledge as a whole,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.31,0:01:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,in other words, curiosity itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.71,0:01:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,may be despised as frivolous and wasteful.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.82,0:01:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,If that happens,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.36,0:01:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't help but feel sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.33,0:02:02.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I choose
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.88,0:02:04.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}to believe.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.41,0:02:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}I believe in all of you
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.56,0:02:08.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and your curiosity.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.84,0:02:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's to your curiosity\Nand that of our newest member!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.80,0:02:15.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Cheers!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.41,0:02:17.99,Default,,0,0,0,,- Cheers!\N- Cheers!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.23,0:02:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}ORB: ON THE MOVEMENTS OF THE EARTH
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.90,0:03:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh man, I spoke too long again.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.26,0:03:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.31,0:04:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you again.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.11,0:04:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what to say,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.15,0:04:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,but I'm very happy\Nthat you invited me here!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.63,0:04:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't be so humble.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.20,0:04:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,We're equals here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.25,0:04:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I have an errand to attend to,\Nso I'll take my leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.30,0:04:17.99,Default,,0,0,0,,But you should enjoy yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.30,0:04:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,They're probably discussing cosmology\Nat that table over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.21,0:04:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It should interest you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.10,0:04:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Cosmology?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.42,0:04:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You came all the way here,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.36,0:04:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,so it would be a shame if you left early.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.28,0:04:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Be sure to stay until the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.89,0:04:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.32,0:04:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then, see you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.08,0:04:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That's where the secret information\NI obtained comes in.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.00,0:04:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,A prominent man named Ibn al-Shatir
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.58,0:04:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,adopted the stance of the Maragha scholars
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.09,0:04:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and refined the uniform motion\Nof Ptolemy's--
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.34,0:04:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,- Oh!\N- Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.80,0:05:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, it's nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.57,0:05:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Please continue.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.38,0:05:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Right. Anyway, what Ibn al-Shatir did was...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.76,0:05:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Oh, no.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.43,0:05:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I forgot to record my observations today.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.57,0:05:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What do I do?{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.06,0:05:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If I go home now,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.11,0:05:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}the meeting will be over\Nby the time I get back.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.50,0:05:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Then again, this is a special day.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.23,0:05:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It won't hurt if I skip\Nmy observations just this once.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.37,0:05:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,...there's another way to look at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.75,0:05:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,- Huh?\N- Sorry, I have to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.06,0:05:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much for today!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.29,0:05:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.84,0:05:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Come again, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.09,0:05:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I will. Farewell!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.47,0:05:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If I'm lucky,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.76,0:05:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I can borrow Father's horse\Nand go back right away.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.01,0:05:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I might make it in time!{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.71,0:05:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm back!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.26,0:06:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.23,0:06:20.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.99,0:06:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? W-What are you...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.18,0:06:27.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.25,0:06:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Man, this is a dilemma.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.22,0:06:32.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I understand how you feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.93,0:06:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You must be confused.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.48,0:06:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Even so, I'd like you to stay calm.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.56,0:06:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,If you deal with it rationally,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.57,0:06:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,this too can be understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.82,0:06:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I have faith in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.49,0:06:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me say first
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.08,0:06:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,that I never intended this to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.21,0:06:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to settle things peacefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.72,0:07:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I'll start from the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.42,0:07:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Recently, I heard a rumor
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.30,0:07:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,that your father possessed\Ncertain materials.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.69,0:07:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,These materials deal\Nwith a revolutionary theory
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.89,0:07:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that could change\Nthe shape of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.84,0:07:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been interested in that theory\Nfor as long as I can remember,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.17,0:07:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,but I had given up hope\Nof ever tracking it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.88,0:07:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I had finally found\Nan entry point.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.24,0:07:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So I proposed sharing the materials
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.08,0:07:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and engaging in joint research.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.79,0:07:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn't a bad offer, I'd say.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.56,0:07:41.29,Default,,0,0,0,,To be honest,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.29,0:07:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,the theory is beyond your father's grasp.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.70,0:07:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Without my intellect and social position,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.18,0:07:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,its value will be lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.68,0:07:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I would have compensated him fairly,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.43,0:07:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and we both would have benefited.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.24,0:08:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's when the problem started.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.76,0:08:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,He refused my offer.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.52,0:08:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Without a second thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.35,0:08:07.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.49,0:08:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,he insisted that the theory\Nconflicted with the prevailing models
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.91,0:08:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and that it might be suppressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.73,0:08:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,"I have a child.\NI can't take on anything dangerous."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.75,0:08:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Those were his words.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.67,0:08:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,He was an awfully fussy man.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.04,0:08:26.37,Default,,0,0,0,,With the right political moves,\Nsuppression can easily be avoided.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.37,0:08:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,But he wouldn't listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.86,0:08:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}No, it was worse than that.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.88,0:08:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}When I tried to convince him,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.89,0:08:35.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}he grew angry.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.62,0:08:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In the end, he said\Nhe would burn the materials.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.44,0:08:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to say,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.40,0:08:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,that left me speechless.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.94,0:08:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Despite all his talk\Nof knowledge and learning,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.40,0:08:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,he was a boor\Nconcerned only with self-preservation.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.48,0:08:55.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I guess I shouldn't\Nspeak ill of your father.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.49,0:08:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I take that back. Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.33,0:09:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,In any case, he grew hysterical,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.71,0:09:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and I thought he might\Ndo something drastic.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.96,0:09:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, I pacified him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.78,0:09:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,In the only way I could.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.47,0:09:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Your father
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.84,0:09:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,kept knowledge to himself\Nand refused to share.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.80,0:09:15.37,Default,,0,0,0,,That is an intolerable sin.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.37,0:09:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,That way of thinking must be eliminated.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.69,0:09:21.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.01,0:09:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The important thing here
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.31,0:09:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,is that the knowledge\Nyour father inherited
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.48,0:09:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,will no longer be lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.41,0:09:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,To pursue the beauty of this world,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.69,0:09:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,sacrifices are unavoidable.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.51,0:09:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Now then, that clears things up, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.17,0:09:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}In the end,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.53,0:09:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}just as he finished his speech,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.08,0:09:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}he was captured by the townspeople.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.34,0:09:51.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}I don't know the rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.64,0:09:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}It's ridiculous, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.46,0:09:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}It all meant so little.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.02,0:09:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}My father{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.68,0:10:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}told me to doubt.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.77,0:10:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}As a result, he trusted no one
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.01,0:10:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}and was killed\Nfor not sharing his materials.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.65,0:10:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}My teacher{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.56,0:10:12.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}told me to believe.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.47,0:10:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,As a result,\Nhe had such faith in his convictions
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.20,0:10:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,that he didn't question murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.00,0:10:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the fate of people\Nwho deal with knowledge.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.10,0:10:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,"Truth" and "learning"\Nare too big a burden for humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.59,0:10:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why university
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.05,0:10:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,is a fool's path.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.22,0:10:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have to choose between them?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.22,0:10:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.82,0:10:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Doubt and conviction.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.72,0:10:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Would it hurt to have both?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.77,0:10:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it would.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.30,0:10:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,They contradict each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.48,0:10:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,St. Thomas Aquinas wrote that knowledge
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.10,0:10:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,is both material
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.19,0:10:56.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and immaterial.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.87,0:11:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Body and soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.07,0:11:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Reason and faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.11,0:11:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Philosophy and theology.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.49,0:11:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Doubt and belief.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.38,0:11:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,These contradictions coexist.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.00,0:11:11.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.87,0:11:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we're human.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.47,0:11:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Human beings are neither God nor beast.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.14,0:11:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,They exist between the two.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.01,0:11:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's exactly why
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.05,0:11:28.97,Default,,0,0,0,,they can accept contradiction,\Nambiguity, and confusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.53,0:11:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, such things provide\Na breather from reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.07,0:11:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Listening to you,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.73,0:11:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,it seems that you no longer\Nfeel God's presence.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.83,0:11:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.78,0:11:43.87,Default,,0,0,0,,you no longer sense what a miracle it is
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.87,0:11:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,that our world exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.88,0:11:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Miracles are chance phenomena\Nthat occur when inevitability rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.10,0:11:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,At the same time,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.67,0:11:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,they are also inevitable phenomena\Nthat occur when chance rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.64,0:12:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You felt those things back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.69,0:12:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\i1}You knew that everything\Nin this world is a miracle.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.07,0:12:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,But as you cast aside\Nexperience and memory,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.86,0:12:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,your past and roots,\Nand finally pain itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.11,0:12:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,you also lost the miraculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.57,0:12:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though that realm\Nis where you truly belong.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.41,0:12:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not for you to decide.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.09,0:12:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know what you should do?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.45,0:12:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have a clue.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.62,0:12:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It's simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.17,0:12:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Look up at the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.81,0:12:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, take a deep breath.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.89,0:12:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,My problems aren't that simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.05,0:12:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.19,0:12:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,But even so, they are not insurmountable.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.98,0:12:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Letters to the Corinthians,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.11,0:12:56.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Chapter 10, Verse 13.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.32,0:12:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,"God is faithful;
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.98,0:13:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and he will not let you\Nbe tempted beyond your ability,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.66,0:13:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,but with the temptation
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.29,0:13:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,he will also provide the way of escape,\Nthat you may be able to endure it."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.30,0:13:16.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Now then,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.62,0:13:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,you showed the courage to speak,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.46,0:13:22.87,Default,,0,0,0,,so I will confess my own secret worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.02,0:13:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,In my case...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.52,0:13:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Long ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.90,0:13:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I left a friend for dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.48,0:13:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,In the course of his work,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.61,0:13:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,my friend committed a terrible crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.24,0:13:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Something irreversible.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.95,0:13:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,As a result,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.63,0:13:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,he died.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.91,0:13:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But it was the very severity of his sin
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.21,0:13:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,that made it important\Nto show him the path of salvation.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.97,0:14:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,What was the correct choice\Nfor me at that moment?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.93,0:14:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I still have no answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.43,0:14:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if I ever will.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.14,0:14:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,However, one thing is clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.36,0:14:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Before today,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.18,0:14:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I had turned a blind eye to my past.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.86,0:14:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,But now I was able to express it\Nin words for the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.39,0:14:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,By doing so, I'll probably suffer\Neven more from now on.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.20,0:14:29.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But at the same time,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.95,0:14:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll believe today was a first step.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.29,0:14:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The same goes for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.06,0:14:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You told me your worries.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.22,0:14:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you can move forward.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.13,0:14:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,God will accept us.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.76,0:14:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And God will always offer us a refuge.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.97,0:14:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}But for that to happen,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.81,0:14:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}we must overcome ourselves
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.64,0:14:59.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and face God with sincerity.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.62,0:15:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,In addition,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.86,0:15:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,we must question in solitude
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.95,0:15:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,whether we are worthy of God's acceptance.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.97,0:15:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,But no matter how much\Nwe struggle with that question,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.29,0:15:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,God will remain silent.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.85,0:15:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.24,0:15:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's what enables us
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.25,0:15:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,to continue thinking, without end.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.22,0:15:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to believe that is happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.77,0:15:33.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.09,0:15:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I have one question for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.61,0:15:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,To obtain bread, one offers coin.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.15,0:15:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,To obtain rights, one offers taxes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.36,0:15:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,To obtain wages, one offers labor.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.45,0:15:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So then,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.94,0:15:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,what must one offer up
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.95,0:15:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,to obtain the truth of our world?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.75,0:15:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.47,0:16:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Go in search of the answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.60,0:16:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.52,0:16:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can resume living in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.48,0:16:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I think going to university{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.44,0:16:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}might be one way to find out.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.49,0:16:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Farewell, and may God bless you.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.62,0:17:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,To pursue the beauty of this world,\Nsacrifices are unavoidable.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.40,0:17:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter what happens,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.56,0:17:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll never criticize your curiosity.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.44,0:17:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Teacher,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.94,0:17:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to pursue the beauty of this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.05,0:17:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,To do so, sacrifices are unavoidable.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.07,0:17:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,To be honest,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.70,0:17:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.95,0:17:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But you couldn't reach beauty{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.04,0:18:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,with the methods you chose.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.79,0:18:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what must be offered up
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.08,0:18:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to know the truth of this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.34,0:18:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}But I'm certain
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.74,0:18:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}that hiding things like my father\Nor eliminating others like you
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.38,0:18:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}is not how it's done.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.39,0:18:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We all lack something.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.09,0:18:23.29,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why we work together.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.29,0:18:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The world is too big\Nof a challenge otherwise.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.74,0:18:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Humans are social animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.61,0:18:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Teacher,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.31,0:18:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I too feel {\i1}thaumazein{\i}.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.26,0:18:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I will continue to affirm that feeling
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.46,0:18:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,in ways different from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.79,0:18:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll doubt as I move forward
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.91,0:18:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and believe as I turn back.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.97,0:18:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,My pursuit of beauty
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.84,0:18:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and inspiration
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.57,0:18:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,will never end.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.40,0:19:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you're back.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.50,0:19:09.05,Default,,0,0,0,,- That took longer than expected.\N- Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.36,0:19:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Please allow me to attend university.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.45,0:19:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.61,0:19:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You're our new applicant.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.49,0:19:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Albert, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.60,0:19:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.42,0:19:28.99,Default,,0,0,0,,In that case, sign here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.93,0:19:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Albert... Brudzewski?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.95,0:19:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.26,0:19:45.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Brudzewo is the name of my hometown.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.79,0:19:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I use that name for my signature.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.33,0:19:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.10,0:19:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, anything will do.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.64,0:19:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Starting tomorrow,\Ntake whatever classes you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.30,0:21:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What? A letter?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.20,0:21:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,For me?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.26,0:21:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. It's addressed to Potocki.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.80,0:21:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Potocki?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.39,0:21:09.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know anyone by that name.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.79,0:21:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, this is definitely the address.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.48,0:21:16.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that is what it says.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.81,0:21:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,But then... could it be intended
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.55,0:21:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,for the previous occupant?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.78,0:21:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, I've never seen\Nanything like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.81,0:21:27.41,Default,,0,0,0,,"Certificate of title."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.41,0:21:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,"In the event that\Nthe following book is published,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.00,0:21:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,you will receive\Nten percent of the profits."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.71,0:21:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It's kind of creepy.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.17,0:21:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Plus, isn't this a weird name for a book?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.42,0:21:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}"On the Movements of the Earth,"{\i} it says.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.64,0:21:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That must be a mistake.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.31,0:21:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}After all, it's the heavens that move.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.40,0:21:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It's way too suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.35,0:21:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,They didn't even send\Nthe book in question.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.11,0:22:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Then again, if it brings me money,\NI'm fine with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.12,0:22:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,On the Movements of the Earth{\i1}, huh?{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.63,0:22:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.77,0:22:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In 1468,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.50,0:22:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Albert Brudzewski enrolled\Nat the University of Kraków at age 23.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.56,0:22:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He would eventually work there\Nas a teacher for 20 years.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.97,0:22:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}His lectures focused mainly\Non mathematics and natural philosophy.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.86,0:22:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}At one point,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.02,0:22:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}he expressed skepticism toward\Nthe traditional geocentric model{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.11,0:22:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}but refrained from drawing conclusions.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.54,0:22:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In 1482,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.03,0:22:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}he wrote a commentary\Non the astronomy textbook of the time,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.61,0:22:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,New Theories of the Planets{\i1}.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.83,0:22:59.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It would go on to be widely read\Nat the university.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.18,0:23:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In 1491,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.19,0:23:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}one of the students\Nwho learned astronomy from his commentary{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.59,0:23:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}was a young man named Copernicus.{\i}
Comment: 0,0:23:24.32,0:23:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}ORB: ON THE MOVEMENTS OF THE EARTH\NTHE END
